From: Eduard Zingerman <eddyz87@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 25 Jun 2025 11:24:12 -0700
Subject: bpf: add bpf_features enum
Patch-mainline: v6.17-rc1
Git-commit: b23e97ffc25294025a68924b6feac9cd431c3eb5
References: jsc#PED-14653

This commit adds a kernel side enum for use in conjucntion with BTF
CO-RE bpf_core_enum_value_exists. The goal of the enum is to assist
with available BPF features detection. Intended usage looks as
follows:

  if (bpf_core_enum_value_exists(enum bpf_features, BPF_FEAT_<f>))
     ... use feature f ...

Signed-off-by: Eduard Zingerman <eddyz87@gmail.com>
Link: https://lore.kernel.org/r/20250625182414.30659-2-eddyz87@gmail.com
Signed-off-by: Alexei Starovoitov <ast@kernel.org>
Acked-by: Hoyeon Lee <hoyeon.lee@suse.com>
---
 kernel/bpf/verifier.c |    6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

--- a/kernel/bpf/verifier.c
+++ b/kernel/bpf/verifier.c
@@ -44,6 +44,10 @@ static const struct bpf_verifier_ops * c
 #undef BPF_LINK_TYPE
 };
 
+enum bpf_features {
+	__MAX_BPF_FEAT,
+};
+
 struct bpf_mem_alloc bpf_global_percpu_ma;
 static bool bpf_global_percpu_ma_set;
 
@@ -24443,6 +24447,8 @@ int bpf_check(struct bpf_prog **prog, un
 	u32 log_true_size;
 	bool is_priv;
 
+	BTF_TYPE_EMIT(enum bpf_features);
+
 	/* no program is valid */
 	if (ARRAY_SIZE(bpf_verifier_ops) == 0)
 		return -EINVAL;
